values: Dust is very small, dry particles of earth or sand.
Some people wear medical face masks to avoid breathing in fine dust and germs.

To dust is to clean or remove dirt, dust or debris from something using a cloth or brush.
Dust is tiny, dry particles of earth, dirt, or other matter that can float in the air and settle on surfaces.
